Preheat your oven to 200°C. Unroll the @Puff Pastry Sheet{1} and lay on a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{}. Prick the pastry all over with a #fork{}. Pop onto the top shelf of the oven until lightly golden all over, ~{12-15%minutes}. Once cooked, remove from the oven and set to one side.

> If the middle has risen, gently flatten the pastry with the back of a spoon!

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{2}. Heat a good glug of @Oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and a good pinch of @Salt{}. Cook slowly, stirring regularly, until soft, sticky and lightly coloured, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> If it looks like the onion is starting to burn, add a little more oil or a small splash of water!

In the meantime, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g}.

Once the onion is nice and soft, stir in a pinch of @?Sugar{pinch} (if you have some). Turn the heat to high and cook, stirring continuously, until golden and sticky, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Remove from the heat.

Using a #spoon{}, spread the caramelised onion all over the puff pastry base, leaving room for a 2-3cm border on all 4 sides! Sprinkle over the cheese then dot the @British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%g} evenly on top.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop back into the oven until the sausage is cooked and beginning to colour, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausage meat is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

== Rocket Salad ==

Just before you are ready to serve, pop the @Wild Rocket{40%g} into a large #bowl{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{for the Dressing}, a pinch of @Salt{} and @?Pepper{}. Toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

When the tart is out of the oven, divide onto plates and serve the salad on the side. Dig in!